<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="73" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="73">Distribution (Fig. 20B), phenology (Table 1) and biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="73">Known only from the type locality of Pakhuis Pass, a road to the east of Clanwilliam leading to the Biedouw Valley. Collected in September. No biological information is available. The pass is rocky and dominated by indigenous fynbos.</paragraph>
